article.headline: Bradley 82, Florida Gulf Coast 74
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Daniel Ruffin scored 16 points on Tuesday to lift Bradley past Florida Gulf Coast University 82-74 in a second-round game of the South Padre Island Invitational. Theron Wilson and Jeremy Crouch each had 13 points and Andrew Warren added 11 points for the Braves (3-1), who play Iowa in the third round Friday. Adam Liddel led the Eagles (1-3) with a game-high 25 points. Landon Adler added 17 points and 11 rebounds for Florida Gulf Coast. The Braves led by as many as 20 points in the first half before heading into the break with a 44-32 advantage. Bradley's bench outscored Florida Gulf Coast's bench 21-14.
